{
  "comment_text": {
    "sn27.1:1.9": "I take <i lang='pi' translate='no'>khāyati</i> as the passive “is said to be”, like the more common <i lang='pi' translate='no'>akkhāyati</i> (<a href='https://suttacentral.net/sn22.102/en/sujato#5'>SN 22.102:5</a>). | <i lang='pi' translate='no'>Kammaniya</i> (“fit for work, workable”) is similar in sense to <i lang='pi' translate='no'>bhabba</i> (“capable”) at eg. <a href='https://suttacentral.net/mn119/en/sujato#29.1'>MN 119:29.1</a>. "
  },
